There are a lot of great independent coffee shops in the area, but this Starbucks has actually ended up being my favorite place to stop in and get a drink. The staff there are the perfect mix of friendly and skilled. If you go more than a couple times you'll end up loving the crew of baristas there, like Ellie, Julia, and the so-called K-dot.  They make the perfect caramel macchiato, and I assume that applies to other drinks as well. And K-dot seems to be constantly working to keep the place clean.  The space itself is also really nice. It's set into the ground, but the big windows bring in plenty of natural light. The large wooden table in the center is a wonderful place to hang out, and you'll get a steady flow of foreign visitors all speaking different languages.  If I had one complaint it is that there are no outlets right at the big wooden table (there are some available at the sides). I guess there can never be the perfect Starbucks, but this one comes pretty close.
